commit_message: Initial import.
Removed TODO (no longer needed).
Move init.rb code to main lib code to make it easier for the plugins to become gem-compatible. Updated references from require_plugin to require in case the plugins become gems.
Removed override of reloadable? since it is no longer used in Edge.
Removed commented out code.

Fixed problem with inherited classes of an acts_as_state_machine class not being able to add events that use new states it has defined. Fixed problem in with_state_scope that causes it to fail if subclasses haven't been loaded yet that include new states (therefore, we can't do a search for those states).
Fixed problems with the arguments for an event not passing through to the entering, entered, and exited event handlers.
Added support for sending args through a guard. Simplified some of the args passing.
Renamed :enter, :after, and :exit state options to :before_enter, :after_enter, and :after_exit. Added :before_exit. Refactored implementation of state callbacks.

Fixed find_all_by_state_id within the StateExtension causing problems when multiple tables are being joined that have a state_id field. Modified find_all_by_state_id within the StateExtension to have a default of :all if the number to select is not specified.
Initial revision.
Updated environment for testing.
Added comments.
Removed associations from models that should have been class-specific. Changed the way saving and updating is done so that exceptions are thrown if they fail.
Initial revision.
Added initial set of unit tests. All event and state names are now referenced as symbols instead of strings.
Added tests for Event and State.
Added tests for StateChange.
Added StateDeadline tests. Fixed foreign key for StateDeadline's state so that it points to state_id instead of to_state_id.
Initial revision.
Improved support for subclasses.
Removed schema.rb Added svn:ignore for schema.rb.
Fixed problems with the finder/count/calculate methods for states. Added the majority of the remaining tests for the usage of acts_as_state_machine.
Fixed problem with saving for new records not being done with a transaction. Added stubs for remaining tests.
Fixed problem with updating a deadline when the deadline already exists. Implemented remaining tests.
Added additional plugin dependencies.
Fixed problem with not searching for all of the possible types of StateDeadline classes when updating an existing deadline.
No longer uses drop_table_if_exists.

Updated to use the new module_creation_helper. Changed the method names exited, exiting, entered, and entering to match their callback equivalents (after_exit, before_exit, after_enter, and before_enter).
Made unique indexes more readable. Fixed formatting.
Removed install.rb files. Added support for RubyForge. Added stubs for READMEs.
Removed role_skeleton dependencies on safe_schema_statements. Unique indexes now follow Rails naming conventions. Removed unused bootstrap folders.
Updated to use new method of running state machine migrations.
Added {state_name}_deadline_passed?. Updated library and tests to use class_associations.
Preparing for tests to not be rails-dependent.
Whoops, rolled back to rails-dependent since migrations are rails-dependent.
Specify the fact that some tests rely on no outer transactions.
Added svn:ignore for pkg,rdoc. Removed unused tasks folders. Updated rake task for rubyforge.
Updated format of s.author for gems.
Remove tasks that are no longer being used. Update to latest method for publishing to RubyForge. Update years in license.
Fix index length for state deadlines.
Add support for sending in symbols/strings to the migration. Add proper :destroy options for State and Event.
Disable clearing of deadlines for now.
Rename acts_as_* to has_*.
Move has_* plugins to a separate folder.
Start migrating references from acts_as_state_machine to has_states. Add ability to specify multiple states at once. Start migrating testing framework to use the plugin_test_helper plugin.
Rename rails_root to app_root. Fix remaining references to the old acts_as_state_machine name. Let dry_validity_asserts reference the local trunk version if it's available.
Fix remaining tests from referencing the old PluginAWeek::Acts module. Update environment configuration to load plugins the proper way (no more manual requires before running the initializer).
Initial release
Add comments.

Moved deadline support into a separate plugin (has_state_deadlines). Added many more unit tests. Simplified many of the interfaces for maintainability. Added support for turning off recording state changes. Removed the short_description and long_description columns, in favor of an optional human_name column. Fixed not overriding the correct equality methods in the StateTransition class. Added to_sym to State and Event. State#name and Event#name now return the string version of the name instead of the symbol version. Added State#human_name and Event#human_name to automatically figure out what the human name is if it isn't specified in the table. Updated manual rollbacks to use the new Rails edge api (ActiveRecord::Rollback exception) Moved StateExtension class into a separate file in order to help keep the has_state files clean. Renamed InvalidState and InvalidEvent exceptions to StateNotFound and EventNotFound in order to follow the ActiveRecord convention (i.e. RecordNotFound). Added StateNotActive and EventNotActive exceptions to help differentiate between states which don't exist and states which weren't defined in the class. Added support for defining callbacks like so:   def before_exit_parked   end  def after_enter_idlingn  endnAdded support for defining callbacks using class methods:n  before_exit_parked :fasten_seatbeltnAdded event callbacks after the transition has occurred (e.g. after_park)nState callbacks no longer receive any of the arguments that were provided in the event actionnUpdated license to include our names.nn

Re-design to be library-agnostic (define state machines on any Ruby class, with integration support for ActiveRecord and DataMapper) * Use a class containing the transition context in callbacks, rather than an ordered list of each individual attribute * Add the ability for the state change action (e.g. +save+ for ActiveRecord) to be configurable * Add the ability to skip state change actions during a transition (e.g. vehicle.ignite(false)) * Only generate the known states for a machine on demand, rather than calculating beforehand * Include states referenced in transition callbacks in the list of a machine's known states * Add support for using real blocks in before_transition/after_transition calls instead of using the :do option * Add support for dynamic to states in transitions (e.g. :to => lambda {Time.now})
